      Family (14)

      Orchidaceae

        Genus (747)

        Dendrobium
          Prev genus | Next genus

          Display options

          Ver. 19.1
          March 1st, 2024

          131.0000 Family Orchidaceae Juss.; Gen. Pl.: 64 (1789), nom. cons.
          over 800 genera, more than 30.000 spp. worldwide, mostly tropical
          Species listed in database: 30459; hybrids: 1408
          = Apostasiaceae Lindl.; Nix. Pl.: 22 (1833), nom. cons.
          = Cypripediaceae Lindl.; Nix. Pl.: 22 (1833)
          = Limodoraceae Horan.; Char. Ess. Fam.: 44 (1847)

          = Pycnanthaceae Ravenna; Onira 12(6): 29 (2011)
          = Vanillaceae Lindl.; Key Bot.: 73 (1835)
          131.6112 Genus Dendrobium Sw.; Nova Acta Regiae Soc. Sci. Upsal. 6: 82 (1799), nom. cons., s. l.
          Distribution: Mostly tropical Asia, especially New Guinea (626), extending to S-Himalaya, Japan, Pacific and Australia. For molecular reasons it is unavoidable to include many previously separated genera (especially Cadetia, Flickingeria and Diplocaulobium), otherwise the genus in traditional sense would be polyphyletic. Any attempts to dismantle it would require worldwide revision and not local treatments.
          Species listed in database: 1577; hybrids: 17

          A complete, synonymic checklist of the Higher Plants of the World

          Version 19.1 (March 1st, 2024)

          Covering 354,262 accepted species,
          8,619 hybrids, 47,813 accepted infraspecific taxa and 995,578 synonyms,
          in total 1,406,272* names

          [*about 25,000 dubious, "unplaced" names and about 4,000 invalid names (Art. 24.3) like "typicus" are deliberately omitted]

          With complete, detailed distribution data (countries and regions) and literature references

          Arranged in linear phylogenetic sequence reflecting true relationships

          Fully searchable and continously updated

          With 38,290 pictures of 15,532 species

          Assembled through 40 years independently from other databases

          In cooperation with Catalogue of Life

          Contact

          Dr. Michael Hassler

          D-76646 Bruchsal
          Germany
